25|$|Some {{statements}} {{are defined as}} hearsay, but may nevertheless be <b>admissible</b> <b>as</b> <b>evidence</b> in court. These statements relate to exceptions to the general rule on hearsay. Some (but not all) exceptions to the hearsay rule apply only when the declarant is unavailable for testimony at the trial or hearing.|$|E
