25|$|Prior {{inconsistent}} statements: Many {{states have}} {{departed from the}} approach of the federal rules with respect to inconsistent statements. Under current law in these jurisdictions, a prior inconsistent statement made by a witness (even when not made under oath at a judicial proceeding or deposition) is <b>admissible</b> <b>as</b> substantive <b>evidence</b> provided the declarant signed the statement.|$|R
